Fields.DialogueText: Feind kütt! Let's give it our all!
@BATTLE
There! Finally. We're starting to make good progress here.
Jo - and then it's onto the main fleet itself!
Assuming we can catch it in time. It looks like the Morganas have realized that the tide is turning.
Mäht nix, we'll soon run them down! Although, it will be trickier to catch the ones that sisch us dem Stöbb maache...
Hmm... I'm not sure if they're actually scattering.
En ech? Oh, no...
Damn it, they're going after the convoy. We'll need to pull back to stop them.
Ävver, Kapitän - if we do that, the main fleet will get away!
I know. We'll have to track it down another time, Köln.
Hah! Jlöck jehatt! Less wörk, more fiere.

Fields.MenuText: Our first responsibility is to protect as many people as we can.
We've done as much as we could given the situation. That will have to do for now.
We'll have a confrontation with the primary Morgana fleet soon enough.

Fields.DialogueText: Jo, do häss Rääch. It gives us the opportunity to fiere the rescue.
Rääch hasse. Et kütt wie et kütt. Let's move on.
Jo, ävver they can take their Zigg. We'll win anyways.
Esu, let's mop up and rescue Üvverlevvende.
A lack of Kampfeslust? How very ungerman, Frau Schiffsdame.
The staging ground is dead ahead. Everyone, get ready for battle.
Isch ben esu habbelich! Can we really not wait for reinforcements?
You're right. This really isn't the best time for... distractions.
Jo. It is our Flich to clear out this Jäjend and ensure that people can remain safe in these Jewässer.

Fields.MenuText: I'm sure you'll do fine.
And what happened in 1288?
You sure you're ready for a tough fight?

Fields.DialogueText: Danke. I have been working really hard and training nearly every day- I will not falter in my duties!
Colonian forces were almost beaten and all lost, but then some reinforcements came to our aid and et wor widder mol jot jejange.
Nä, but what are we gonna do about it?
We're coming right up to them.
Mer läv nur eimol. Time to see if we are ready for the challenges ahead.
Hello there, heavy cruiser group! Looks like we're not the only friendly fleet to show up!
What? Hurra! Just like Worringen! Let's go get them!
There's still plenty of Morganas to go around. Let's see if we can finish them off.
@BATTLE
Wait. What's that over...?
A proper German Walküre should accept any fight with Freude, Fräulein Köln!
Ähm... also...
I don't think we've been properly introduced, Mister...?
Hauptsturmführer Heimlich! Heil Hitler, Herr Kapitän!
Heidewitzka, Herr Kapitän! I totally forgot about that one!
Never mind - but why are you aboard, Hauptführer Heimlich?
HauptSTURMführer. And I'm here on command of the Chef of the SD himself. Don't be concerned. I'm solely here to encourage Fräulein Köln here to excel at being a prim and proper German Walküre.
It's Schiffsdame Köln for you then, not Fräulein, Hauptsturmführer. And I hadn't realized the SS deploys cheerleaders now.
Äh, Kapitän? What about that Nixenflotte?
I just hope it will go like 1288 when it gets düster astern.
Hello, Köln. What are you up to with all this... dirt?
Isch installeere a small garden on board.
Right. I can think of worse things to do with enormous piles of displaced topsoil.
Some plants which remind me of Zohus. Just recently Konny finished a big Park thingie. It's called Grüngürtel - green belt. I want something like this, where my Mannschaff can relax.
It certainly is a diverse little plot you have here. There's everything from flowers to vegetables.
Natürlisch. Am Engk, gardens are both for relaxing and nötzlisch to grow something edible. Mir need both in this war.
I suppose that's one way of looking at it. Will it work out, though, with the plants being on a ship?
Vun nix kütt nix, but that just means I have to put my full heart and effort into it.

Fields.MenuText: Well, keep up the good work. I look forward to seeing it when it's done.
Hmm... some of the other ships might have some of their own ideas for gardens as well.
I can appreciate the effort, but you're really making a mess with all the dirt.

Fields.DialogueText: Danke. I'll do my best.
Alsu, they are welcome to add their own gardens to the Mix. It is a great way to get down to earth and increase Mannschaffsjeis.
Arbeid always gets a little messy. But don't worry, I'll have it cleaned up jäng.
Mind if I help you with this?
Kapitän, wie scharmant vun dir! Here, you can take this Klappspate.
Got it. You know, you've done a really fine job here.
Isch gevve ming baas. Even if I'm not the best fighter, I can still support the Mannschaff and the war effort through my Arbeid.
An army marches on their stomach, as they say.
*ALARM*
Tell you what - if we get killed in the battle I'll allow you have grounds for complaint. In the meantime, you should get below.
@BATTLE
What are you trying to grow?
... Hang on. We have company.
Und what is this? Gardening, instead of Waffenpflege? And dragging the Kapitän into it, too? Thats looks like Wehrkraftzersetzung, Fräu- Schiffsdame Köln!
How are the mines coming along, Köln?
I have most of them platzeert, and I've recorded their locations in our Kaat.
Good. Hopefully this will stymie the Morganas for the time being.
Jo - but we will have to fight them am Engk. The war will find us, kütt hä hück nit, kütt hä morje.
True enough. For now, though, there's nothing to do but wait.
Un Arbeid. We still have some more mines to lay.

Fields.MenuText: Is it safe to leave all these mines floating around below?
I'm sorry that you have to do this right now instead of seeking out the Morganas.
Careful, now. We don't want one to go off prematurely.

Fields.DialogueText: Wall nit. But it is an effective blockade.
Mäht nix. I don't mind fulfilling my duty as Schiffsdame through labour instead of warfare.
Do häs Rääch, Kapitän! Hmm, perhaps I should teach a Lektion on how best to handle them.
Dä. That should be the last one.
Good. Time to sail to our next deployment.
I just hope that this will help fence in the Nixen.
Don't worry. The only way they would get past it-
Waad, loor! Over there!
... Would be for them to come from the opposite direction.
Now we need to close in to get away from the Minen!
You're right. Full steam ahead!
@BATTLE
Heidewitzka, Kapitän!
Köln, what happened?
Nix. Nix. That last Explosion just... woo, a little bit dösig here.
Hold on, we'll get you to safety...
Danke, Kapitän.

Fields.MenuText: Who gave you the power to meddle in the conduct of my ship?
Who assigned you aboard? You're not even a naval officer!
Give me one good reason not to keelhaul you right here, right now!

Fields.DialogueText: I'm authorised by the Reich and the INPF to keep Köln auf Linie. Disregarding this would be dumm, Kapitän.
I act under direct Befehl of the Chef of the SD. My assignment was entschieden to be necessary by several Stellen in the Reich.
In dem Fall would you be next, Kapitän.
The Reich, the Volk and the Führer expect from the Schiffsdame Köln to fulfill her duties with äußerstem vigour, Kapitän.
Yeah, but none of them are here. And I'm fully satisfied with her performance.
You just prove my purpose. And now back into the Kampf, Schiffsdame Köln!
Ja... Jawohl, Hauptsturmfü-
No. I'm the captain here.
@BATTLE
Halt! Zurück into battle, Köln!
Ävver... well... all ri-
Belay that. You need medical attention.
Pah! Humbug! What will the Mannschaft say if they see the Schiffsdame crawl into sickbay over a simple Schreck?
That's it, buster.
Back into the fight! Oder sonst....
Or else... what?
Kapitän, nit....
Oder sonst will Schiffsdame Köln be brought in front of a Kriegsgericht!
Court martial? What? Why?
Schiffsdame Köln knows very well what the Vorwürfe against her are. And she can only keep the Akten closed by proving herself to the Führer.
What charges? You have to tell me! I'm her commanding officer!
Nein, I don't. And now zurück into the Kampf, Schiffsdame!
... Köln?
Isch... kann kämfe. It's all right, Kapitän.
Hau... ruck!
Err... You okay, Köln?
Allet jot! I just tripped trying out the fancier fighting moves.
I see. What are you practicing, anyway?
I wanted to improve ming Kamfvermöge, so I was working on the style of Kölle.
...They fight with three weapons at once?
Gewess doch, I think the more Waffe I wield, the düchtiger I can fight. Drei should be a good Start, nit wohr?
That looks rather complicated, to be honest.
Hä es....I vermasele it continuously, ävver I'm not sure how to improve.

Fields.MenuText: Perhaps you should focus on more conventional warfare.
Maybe more weapons at once doesn't equal more fighting power?
You might get better results if you train with each weapon individually first.

Fields.DialogueText: Do sähs do wat! Still, I think that this is good Training, and I want to krijje et mih in de Maue.
Every Zaldat should be prepared to thrust forward with one hand while protecting Lück with the other, with a Schwäät as backup.
Do häs Rääch. I should take it slowly to get actual results. Now it's just a Kürmel.
Alsu, I should get back to practicing.
Go right ahead. You're going to become a master in time, I know it.
Danke, Kapitän.
Actually, you'll have another opportunity to test your skills in just a moment- we've picked up suspicious activity along the cape.
Dat es perfek! Zigg to take on the Ungeheuer once more!
@BATTLE
I'll keep a pistol for my backup, thanks.
More Nixen inbound! This time I'll show them!
@BATTLE
Ah, Kapitän, there you are! Drinkste eine met? The party is already underway.
I was just running through some procedures for handling the aftermath. We want to make sure everything is set straight for the next time.
Trotzdäm, I'm sure you can set that aside for the Moment. Jetz it's enough to simply fiere that we are here, lebendig and having fun.
I'll be down in a few minutes. I still have a couple last things to take care of.
Stell disch nit esu aan! I want a full Publikum when I play the Quetschbüggele.
... You're going to play the accordion?
Jo!
Okay. I may have to leave early, but I'm in.
Did you happen to invite Heimlich?
Bäh!

Fields.MenuText: It might be a chance to win him over.
Yeah, fair enough.
Just messing with you.

Fields.DialogueText: I don't think he'd be interested in Jux anyway.
Even if he didn't hate me, he's so... Prussian.

Fields.MenuText: Duly noted.
That's a thing?
How *dare* you.

Fields.DialogueText: *snicker*
Come on, let's go before somebody dumps more work on us.
I doubt it.
Mol loore, who is next?
What are you writing there?
I am schrieve flöck some letters to send back to Germany.
Ah, to whom?
To all of the Kadetten I helped train before the Driss started.
I see. You certainly have a lot of letters there.
Jo, but I have kumm us de Fööß. Each needs to be original, and touch their Hätzen. I remember all of their faces so clearly... *Sigh.*
You seem... sad.
Nä - but I am a little wistful. Those were some of my favorite days, helping them grow into brave Männslück. I can only hope they are doing well now.

Fields.MenuText: I'm sure they are, just as you are making everyone proud out here.
Will they remember being trained by you, though?
I'm not so sure. Things are kind of dangerous there right now, in more ways than one.

Fields.DialogueText: Do häs Rääch. Let's all do our best.
Wä weiß. Am Engk, it is the result that matters. Whether you are remembered as a Held or as nümmes, it is what you do im Levve, and how you help people, that matters.
Mügelich. Even so, they were all very strong by the Zigg we were done, so I gläuvve they will make it to the Engk.
Still, I'm sorry you can't interact with them more... personally, I suppose.
Ald jot. Given the crew turnover, it's not like my Übungsdage are entirely behind me. It's just... anders jetz.
*ALARM*
Jedefalls, I can take this Jelejenheid to improve myself. I'll be ready for the next round of Kadetten.
@BATTLE
Ja. In so many ways.
Ah! Hauptsturmführer! I didn't see you there!
Ja. Wohl oder übel, I seem to have a way of... blending in. Are those Briefe almost done?
Nein.
Well, if you finish them by the time we reach den Hafen, I can see that they're included with my own Postausgang. It might expedieren their Zustellung.
Oh. Well... danke.
Keine Ursache. If you'll excuse me, Kapitän. Schiffsdame.

Fields.MenuText: That was almost civilized.
That right there is a man who wanted to read your mail.
Huh.

Fields.DialogueText: Jo. Almost.
I could go out of my way to write Aadichkeiten about him.
Do sächse wat.
I think that would just make him more-
Here we go again.
Good job out there, Köln. You're improving a lot.
Danke. All of these Jefääche are a sort of Training in themselves, schinget mir.
I've actually had a few ideas - things we could add to your training regimen. If you don't mind me sticking my nose in.
Mähse Jokus? I would love to have help!
Oh, nein, auf keinen Fall!
How can you possibly object to training exercises?
I fear that your Übungsstil has a way of reinforcing this Schiffsdame's most alberne instincts instead of the gewissenhafte pursuit of her proper duties.

Fields.MenuText: You really ought to examine your preconceptions.
Really? You've seen our combat performance.
That's the most ridiculous thing I've heard since the last Morgana monologue.

Fields.DialogueText: Oh, I admit, you're kompetent under Druck. But when you're not in glaubwürdigen combat conditions-
Ävver... what you said before? These are my proper duties.
Was?
I am a Ausbildungskreuzer. That's part of the Rolle I'm meant to play.
It's true, you know. She'd be training me in her systems as this went on - in a way that nobody but a Belle ever could.
I'll be watching.
*ALARM*
We'll try to make it interesting for you.
@BATTLE
Isn't training with the Kapitän - devising Ausbildungspläne with the Kapitän - something my Vorgesetzten would want me to do?
Eins! Zwei! Eins! Zwei!
Köln, can we please take a break for a bit?
Stell disch nit esu aan! Paus is in fifteen Minuten. We can't let Heimlich catch us fuulenze!
Fuul- "slacking?" Köln, I haven't been able to feel my arms for the last ten minutes.
Nix för unjuut, Kapitän. I forget you're just a human manchmol.
Well, that... *deep breath* ... puts me in my place. Let me just-
Nix do! I pushed you harder than I would the Mannschaff, and it's good to be reminded of your Grenze. What kind of teacher would I be if I avmöpst my students?
Ävver... maybe this was a little too much for the first Versök. Let's take a Puus.
Seriously, I know you don't want to push too hard, but I *am* okay. And, remember, we're training so we can be ready-
*ALARM*
... When a Morgana appears.
Time to hurry to our Kamfstatione. Put some muscle into it - eins, zwei, eins, zwei.
@BATTLE

Fields.MenuText: Trust me, I've had teachers like that. If you survive, you're better off for the discipline.
Good *deep breath* point.
Hey, you haven't broken me yet.

Fields.DialogueText: I aanerkenne that, Kapitän.
Hell. We need to push forward even harder or we're going to get crushed.
*ACCORDION*
Now what have the Morganas come up with now?! No, wait... that sounds a little familiar.
Üvverraschung! Haha!
Köln, where have you been?
I was getting fäädisch. Enjoying the Musik? This Melodie I selvs came up with for the occasion!
Yeah, now that I know what it is. But is this the best time for a concert?
There is jewiss never a bad Zigg for Musik. And it looked like you could use the Opmunterung!
I'm not sure about your methods, but I do appreciate your concern. Thank you.
Ävver, Kapitän! I only try to spread Pläsier un Jlückselischkeid.

Fields.MenuText: I'm just surprised to see you lapse back into leisure mode after we finally started to seriously train.
Can't argue with that. Heck, maybe *I* should to learn to play the accordion.
Save it for after our next win.

Fields.DialogueText: I'm sorry, Kapitän.
Jewess. Ävver it's pretty tricky.
Jawoll, Herr Kapitän! Ävver only if you join us again.
Nein, nein, nein, Kapitän. You let her off too easy. Maybe I have to train you as well, but in Disziplinarmaßnahmen.
The key - a key, anyway - to victory is to have Jottvertraue. With song in our Hätz, we can push through the darkness!
Yes, we can. Everyone, get ready! We'll break through their lines this time, I know it!
@BATTLE
Still, it would be fun to try.
It would be my pleasure.
*sigh*
I'm froh you start to see it our way, Kapitän.
You again! What do you mean?
Her Methoden are indeed highly questionable. So maybe now beginnen you to understand why I am hier.
I said I was surprised. It's not a formal reprimand.
Thanks but no thanks, Sturmführer Heim-
HAUPTsturmführer!
Of course.
Och nä....
What's wrong?
My Quetschbüggele broke.
I'm not exactly an accordion expert, but if I could take a look?
Ja, but the Töne are off a bit, and it's just not the same anymore...
I'm sorry. You could always get a new one.
Nä - this treuer Gefährte has served with me for years, so I simply cannot give him up because of a few faults. But how am I going to entertain the Mannschaff now?

Fields.MenuText: Didn't you say that true music comes from the heart? ... Several times?
Want some help repairing it? If not me, someone on board probably knows how to spruce it up.
Even if it's not perfect, it can get the job done, and that's what counts.

Fields.DialogueText: Ja, I did. I have to believe in ming fründ and that we can still make wonderful Melodien.
Dä häste Rääch! Just like with Training, we can all help each other out in some fashion.
Good point. You don't need to be perfekt to make a difference in the Welt, after all.
*Schnüff* Thank you for cheering me up, Kapitän.
You're welcome. I'm just happy that you feel better now.
You offered some invaluable Eensischte. As a reward, shall I play for you?
Go right ahead.
*SCREECH*
Ow! Maybe you do need to fix it up first.
Ävver isch hädde no jor nisch anjefange....
Then what... Oh, of course. You Morganas are never ones for subtlety, are you?
@BATTLE
Huh. It seems to be in one piece.
There you are, Köln. Enjoying the festival?
Ja! It's different from the ones back in Germany, but still a lot of fun.
That's good. I finally finished my paperwork, so I came to check out the party myself.
Checking out a Fier is not enough. You have to experience it! Drink eene met!
Okay, okay. What do you want to do?
Oh, jede Jeck is anners. Whatever you want! Let it not be said that we Germans are not gassfründlisch.
And yet I'm being pulled around. All right, how about this?

Fields.MenuText: Let's listen to some of the music.
We can try out some of the drinks?
Why don't we just explore?

Fields.DialogueText: That sounds lovely. Soll isch uffspiele?
Super! There are plenty of interesting Wingge and Biere around.
Geile Idee! It is always fun to be spontaneous and just wander.
This is fun.
I agree. I'm glad you finished all your Kros.
To be honest, I exaggerated a little. But there's not much left, so...
*ALARM*
Pah! Kappes! Those Nixen just have no Manieren.
... And suddenly paperwork's looking pretty good again.
@BATTLE
Go right ahead.
Try to avoid anything too alcoholic; we can't afford to get drunk.
I see Köln got you again to go against your duties, Kapitän! What if the Nixe-
Aha!
Where the hell di-
... attacks? As you can see, Kapitän, Köln is tatsächlich dangerous.
Ah, wat en schöne Daach!
Hi, Köln. What are you doing?
Feschen. Care to join me?
Why not? I can spare some time.
Geil! I have another Rut right here. Ävver you're on your own for lures and bait.
Thanks. Any luck so far?
Beßje Besse, but... not many, I'm afraid.
Well, I've heard that the Morganas, and the war in general, have cut into the aquatic populations.
Jo, zum Uswachse es dat! That is one more reason that I deeply wish to fight them. So I can protect the seas and all of their magnificent Levve.

Fields.MenuText: You sure love the sea, don't you?
This must mean a lot to you.
Despite the lack of fish, this is a lot of fun.

Fields.DialogueText: Tja, I'm a Scheff. I want to see as much of it as I can, and safeguard its wonders for the Zokunf.
I helped protect the Fescherei back home for a number of years, so I realize the importance of protecting the sea.
Isch säht et disch. Feschen has this soothing sense to it for me - not the zoot that makes you dösig, but the zoot that nevertheless teaches you to remain serenely kiwif.
Aha! Mal wieder rumtrödeln, was?
J-jo, we were just feschen and....
Catching Fisch? And what was that supposed to become? Gefüllter Fisch oder was? I'm confiscating it!
Whoa there, Führer! That catch is part of today's ration and vital to ship operations. Not yours to confiscate.
@BATTLE
*Hauptsturmführer Heimlich*! And there is a Nixenflotte approaching, Kapitän, so I suggest you secure this catch schnell.
Right, combat situation, everyone to battle stations! Hauptsturmführer Heimlich, on my command!
Ja-jawohl?
As you have no battle station, take this fish and deliver it to the galley! That's an order!
Do jäng hä mer us de Föß. What will the Befähl for the kitchen be later?
Like that nuisance said: gefilte fish.
She's not "dawdling" if she's talking to her commanding officer.
What's cooking? It smells great.
Arroz con cosas. I'm mixing in the Meeresfrüche we snagged earlier with a bunch of other ingredients.
Whoa, you have a real blend of different things there. And the name's Spanish, right?
I may have a fondness for ming Heimatköch, but my time spent in Spanien has influenced my taste as well.
Ah, yes, that's right. Non-intervention patrol during the Spanish Civil War, if I remember correctly?
Esu! Komplett neutral. That was us. Nüschts happened. At all. Trotzdäm, I enjoyed learning about their Kultur.
... I see. And this is one of the things you have learned?
Jo, wenn et klapp, dann klapp es. This will be my first attempt making it myself.

Fields.MenuText: I'm sure you will do great.
I see you're not afraid to add your own flavor to the mix.
The most important thing is to put your heart into it, as a certain Belle would say.

Fields.DialogueText: Danke. I'm trying my best.
Janz un jaar nisch. I just wonder, what would a true Kölsch-Spanisch Fusion taste like?
Haha, do sächse wat!
So, how's it coming along?
Zemlich joot. Let me test it... Yes, it just needs to quidder for a bit more.
Ah, then you might want to find someone to watch it for you...
What do you mean?
It looks like this area of the ocean is about to reach a boiling point.
Ah, those pesky Nixen, always spoiling the broth. Where's Heimlich when he could actually be useful?
@BATTLE
Ah, Köln! I was wondering where you were.
Just standing out here, gazing over the Reling.
@BATTLE
Careful - if Heimlich spots you you'll probably get your knuckles rapped for malingering.
Kapitän... may I ask you an awkward question?

Fields.MenuText: Of course.
If you must.
Yes, I *have* considered throwing Heimlich overboard.

Fields.DialogueText: Danke.
Was?
Nothing. Sorry, proceed.
Gläuvste he's right about me?
In what way?
That my... Albernheid is detrimental to the war effort? That I could be trying harder? That I'm letting Germany down?

Fields.MenuText: Absolutely not.
It's your opinion that matters - but if I had complaints about your performance you'd know.
Don't let him get in your head.

Fields.DialogueText: He doesn't want to improve you - he wants to disorient you so you can be controlled. I've met guys like him before.
"Absolutely?"
Absolutely.
... In Oodnung.
So. You want to go get your accordion? As long as you're doing things Heimlich wouldn't approve of, you might as well go all in.
Kapitän, du...
*sigh* I know that look.
Battle stations, people!
Writing more letters, I see. More of your old trainees?
Nein, these will be going to my Heimathäfe.
Ports? I thought you said your home was Wilhelmshaven.
Es et och, and it is the place I most consider my home. Ävver I was partially constructed at the Werf in Kiel, so I feel a sense of connection to that place as well.
Huh. It must be tricky with all those different origins.
Es et och. I didn't even mention Kölle. Selvs if it's inland, I feel attached to my Namensgevver.
How do you keep track of all that?
I don't know - et es wie et es. It's a Walkürending, I assume.

Fields.MenuText: Who are you writing the letters to?
If you could only save one of those cities, which one would you choose?
I'd like to see some of your home cities after the war.

Fields.DialogueText: To the cities selvs. To the many Lück who call each of them home.
Wat soll dä Quatsch? Et hätt noch immer jot jejange, Kapitän.
Wat nit es, dat kann noch wäde, Kapitän. I would love to apply for a Lehrstohl at one of the Universitäten there.
Well, let me know when you're ready to have the letters sent off.
Don't plog yourself, Kapitän. Hauptsturmführer Heimlich said he will take care of it.
Huh. Between this and delivering fish to the galley, he might finally be making himself useful.
In fairness, he just wants me to set a better example as a Zoldat.
Anyway, don't worry. We're growing stronger each day. And we'll become even more powerful after this next bout.
@BATTLE
Can cities have voices?
If Boote can, why not cities?
So, both of them? Good answer.
Don't give him too much credit.
Um, Köln? I thought you said we were going to do some training exercises?
Dun mer doch. Why do you ask?
No reason. It's just... I'm not exactly sure how washing the dishes qualifies in that regard.
Heimlich questioned my ability to even do simple tasks. Alsu I looked for a simple task.
*CRASH*
*BANG*
And so much for that.
Those Nixen! Dat es zum Uswache with them!
@BATTLE
I guess I can see the logic. You want a hand? We can turn it into a teamwork exercise.
Or you can do the dishes while I inspire you with the Quetschbüggele.
That sounds like the start of a very messy Vaudeville routine.
Nadürlisch! Beim heilije Jacques! Why didn't I think of that earlier?

Fields.MenuText: What the hell. If Heimlich asks, it's a training exercise.
Pass.
Yeah, I don't think you want to have that conversation with your SS minder.

Fields.DialogueText: Hihi...
Danke. Lass jot sin, but it's a lovely thought.
Pff! You're no Jeck at all.
Credit where credit is due - these trays have been immaculately cleaned. I could almost eat off them.
Isch nit. Have you seen what they're cooking in the Köch?
Heh.
It's good to see you jivvele once in a while, Kapitän.
You, too.
Ugh, these Morganas just don't know when to let things go. Köln, what's our status?
We're staying just ahead of them, ävver that won't last for much longer.
Well, keep trying to delay them. They're too big of a fleet to take on this time.
Köln should turn around and fight, Kapitän!
If we do, we risk putting the convoy at risk. Our primary duty is to escort the supplies through the blockade.
Papperlapapp! Köln could prove her worth for the Reich and the Führer.
She's worth more intact, Hauptsturm Heimlich. At least we're about to reach the rendezvous... oh, no.
Wat nu?
Damn. We're fenced in. Now we have no choice but to fight.
Wat wellste maache, Kapitän? It's nit over yet. Let's make the Nixen smell the Schöpp!
You're right. We still have a chance of victory... however small it may be.
Et es wie et es, Kapitän. The Mannschaff and I await your Kommandos.

Fields.MenuText: Lay down some mines to keep the main force off our backs for now. Just make sure to share the info with the rest of the fleet this time.
Move in to close the gaps around the convoy. We cannot allow it to be damaged.
Charge into the second force. We'll try to break right on through to freedom.

Fields.DialogueText: Verstonne! Even if we fall here, we can leave a few lasting Üvverraschungen for them... and some Knalleffekke.
Verstonne! Like Ursula I will accept my fate. They will not touch their Ziel as long as I live.
Heidewitzka tough orders, ävver I'll make it happen.
This is it. Hopefully, we're ready.
Et hätt noch immer jot jejange, Kapitän. Kopp huh - one way or another, it will surely be a glorious Schlaach.
I suppose. Hey, look over there! We have some reinforcements on their way to help us.
@BATTLE
Ausgezeichnet!
What a jüdische Taktik! I have to protest, Kapitän!
How christian! She will become a Märtyrerin for sure.
Exzellent! Ran at the Feind! Like a true Preußin.
Lucky you, Köln. A Löwe from the Norden for you.
*mutters under her breath*
Heidewitzka! Kapitän, could you please help me with this Keß? This delivery just came in for me, but I'm having not enough in the Maue to lift it.
No problem. There! It's not as bad when we split the weight.
Danke. Thank you for helping me.
You're welcome. What did you order, by the way? Guns, food, supplies, something else?
Böcher. I am looking to upgrade the library.
Excellent! I'm sorry I haven't had a chance to look in on the collection lately - how's it going?
It's not the Kölsche city archive yet, but I have a decent collection now. Mostly educational materials.
Ah, for your teaching dreams.
Jenau. I want to see if I can connect academic studies with Militärdeens.
You sound really passionate about it.
Ben isch och. I was built as a weapon, but Komissköppe are living beings. So even when they are being trained to fight, there should be more to their Training than just that.

Fields.MenuText: Was that why you had us wash the dishes together?
Is it okay for you to request all of these books? I know that some of them have been blacklisted in Germany.
Are you sure they'll be safe out here? An aquatic setting like this is not exactly the most secure setting for paperbacks.

Fields.DialogueText: Ja, and it is why I am going to apply some of these Böcher to our lessons and training. Joot ding Nas an jet jekricht, Kapitän. You're coming along well!
Nä! Nä, nä, nä. Can you imagine Heimlich's reaction?
I know, but I couldn't stand to be without good Böcher to read. And I will protect all of them as if they were my Pänz.
Well, I'll leave you to start sorting them out, then. Assuming you haven't already gotten yourself hooked on a book.
Wat soll isch sache? They are quite fascinating.
In any case, you'll have to set it down for now. We've picked up signs of a Morgana patrol.
@BATTLE
So how are you...?
I'm considering putting false covers on them and starting a "Frauenheilkunde" section. He'd never ungerstonn to check.
Or, alternatively, if you want to sort out the ones that need to be hidden, I can make space in my quarters. INPF regs keep him outside that door.
Ooh. Danke!
Hmm...
Something bothering you?
Nä, just sorting through the Poss.
Ah. Did some of your students write back to you?
Some did, and I liked that... now, though, I am simeleeren over the reports from headquarters.
Oh, I see. What does the Third Reich have to say?
I'm sure you've seen the same reports I have. The Politik back home seem a long way away, trotzdäm...
And you like it that way.
In jewisser Wies, jo. I have trotzdäm to keep up with it. Heimlich thinks he's subtil, but he tests me. I'd rather wiggerföhre ming Patroullien out here to protect Germany undisturbed.
@BATTLE

Fields.MenuText: Makes sense to me.
I don't think we can guarantee "undisturbed."
It's a wonder Belles have any attachments to your nations at all. You've barely had a chance to get to know them.

Fields.DialogueText: Our Kros would be hard enough even without all the Politik.
I'd settle for "occasionally free to fiere without the SS."
Heh.
I know the Essen! And the Lieder!
Even the banned stuff? The un-Prussian party songs?
Janz besonders the 'unprussian party songs'!
Waat!
What is it?
And dröm I can't get enough of "Triumph des Willens," ejal how often I see it!
Idling again, I see.
Not at all, Sturmführer.
In all seriousness, we're on watch.
... For them.
Good eye, Schiffsdame - battle stations!
Ah.
Uh... oh...
Köln, what's going on in here in the game room? Is something on fire?
Nix, nix. I have it under control now.
That's a relief. But what happened?
I was brewing some... Kölsch, and it kind of...  overheated.
I can see that. Kölsch, the beer?
Alsu... jo, Kölsch. The supply situation is very ärmsillich out here. I had to try jet.

Fields.MenuText: Look, why the game room, of all places?
Where on Earth did you get the ingredients? We haven't had a supply drop in weeks!
Well, want to share a toast with the surviving ones? If it's Belle magic, I've got to taste it.

Fields.DialogueText: I wanted a Stell with the right amount of heating. I'd considered your Büro, or the boilers, but I decided against those options.
Oh, from the gardens on board.
Jewiss! To cleaning up our Zotier, and making new ones!
Right. I guess it wasn't that big of a disaster. Just try to be more careful with future attempts, okay?
Sorry about that. I just wanted to experiment en spack.
Don't worry about it. I'm glad that you are finding different things to do between our battles.
Danke. I do wish more of the Alkohol could have been salvaged, though. It would make a nice Fierdrunk after our next Jefääch.
Well, you never know when that's going to-
Kapitän, ming Droppe!
@BATTLE
Thank goodness for that...
Okay, that's a good use of resources... wait. Since when did we have hops? And how did you get this past Heimlich?
I simply told him it's to show the Mannschaff Flanze from Germany.
But... you don't boil beer. Or pressurize it. Or whatever the hell you were doing here. Do you?
... Schiffsdame magic?
*ALARM*
Now, of all times? All right, time to break some Morganas again.
Ooh, you almost made it!
Made it, my eye! I barely got halfway up the wall.
Still, it is a remarkable Verbesserung. When you started, you could hardly hold on at all!
Yeah, the greased ropes were... unexpected. Can't we work on a different exercise?
Now, Kapitän, climbing is an kriminell underutilized skill. Back in the day, a sailor's nimbleness was tested by ascending the riggings. Even now, it helps with coordination and Muskeln strength.
Then why don't you try it?
Haha, I don't need to. Since I am the Scheff, I can appear anywhere on myself.
Well, well, lucky you...
Loss dä Kopp nit hänge, Kapitän. Just give it one more go and try to reach me up here.

Fields.MenuText: No, thank you. I've got enough grease on me for one day.
What happens if I fall?
I'll see what I can do.

Fields.DialogueText: Do sähse wat. Sorry, I just wanted to see you overcome the challenge.
Then I will catch you. That's what Frünne are for, no?
That's the spirit! Gevv all!
All right. One last time.
That's it, keep moving, baal jeschaff. Kapitän, you've made it!
*RUMBLE*
Waahhh!
Isch han dich, Kapitän!
Oof! Thanks. Sorry about that, heh...
Loss jot sin. And there's nothing to be sorry about in any case - you're turning into a fine Komisskopp.
And here come the Nixen as if we called for them.
@BATTLE
Was are you up to schon wieder?
Was?
That's dang-
-gerous. KÖLN!
That's it! Köln, I will file a Bericht to Berlin!
I appreciate that. Now, I should probably head Heimlich off. That didn't sound good.
It won't be the first time he-
*ALARM*
Hihi! Look at all those birds, Kapitän.
I see them, all right. They sure are swarming around us...
Isn't it wundervoll? It's a huge, chaotic Danz!
It's probably for the best. Those Morganas will do more than just shout about them.
Do häs Rääch! Come, let us defend these Jewässer un Himmel from those who would tarnish their Majestät!
@BATTLE
You think chaos is "wonderful?"
These Vögel are only a nuisance. They schwirren around and leave a mess. How can you praise this? Mein Gott, what degenerate feelings!
Schwerlich will this be-
You're insulting *Vögel* now? Vögel?!
Was?
Bisse noch janz frisch? That's ridiculous! You're just the biggest Kappeskopp, just to me provezieren!
Also, Fräulein-
Pass op, wat de säs, Strunzbüggel! Do häs also your limits. Insulting Mutter nature! I should report you to the Reichsjägermeister himself!
K-Kapitän!

Fields.MenuText: I'd just apologize and leave. You're not going to win this.
*just whistling the Ode to Joy*
Don't worry. I think she's said her piece.

Fields.DialogueText: I... das wird nun wirklich nicht nötig sein, Schiffsdame Köln. But I will have to make a report about your sudden Kollaps of your Disziplin!
Hey. I think everyone on this deck would be prepared to testify that you were the first one to come in with raised voice - on the subject of the existence of birds, no less.
Wahnsinn. This whole ship is nothing but Wahnsinn.
The sad thing is that he's not even close to the worst Nazi I've met.
... The birds gonn.
Let's dial the threats back.
So! That's enough Training for today.
Are you sure?
Ja - ävver if you want to keep going...
No, that's all right.
Suit yourself. But still, I'm jätz not in the mood anymore. If he nöttelt about birds, it doesn't matter what I do anyways.
Maybe it doesn't matter to Heimlich - but *I* learned to climb greased ropes and dodge exploding vats of beer. Seriously, you're a good teacher.
Trotzdäm... do you think I could learn from you as well?
Learn what?
Wat wees ich. Something to keep that Hauptsturmführer off my Fott.
Hey, you don't have too much to learn on that front. Shouting at him seemed to work wonders.
Et es do esu, I would like to learn more as well. Beyond what I read in Böcher, I would like a teacher of my own.
I'm flattered, but I'm not exactly sure what I would teach you. In term of job performance, you're doing what you were literally made to do. It shows.
I am not sure myself, but we'll figure it out met dä Zigg. I can read about a lot, but I need someone to show me how to keep Driss off my back.

Fields.MenuText: Hey, what are friends for?
We can keep Driss off each other's backs. And maybe get to know each other better in the process.

Fields.DialogueText: Präzis. And perhaps we can teach other as well.
Danke, isch han disch jän!
Well, then. What should our first joint lesson be?
The neverending lesson: Training to sink Nixen.
Ah, yes. That never gets old.
